description: Add or updates the evaluations for process checks. This API checks if the rule is a process check when the name of the Config rule is provided.

parameters.name: ConfigRuleName
parameters.description: The name of the Config rule.

parameters.name: ExternalEvaluation
parameters.description: An ExternalEvaluation object that provides details about compliance. The evaluated compliance resource type. Config accepts AWS::::Account resource type. The evaluated compliance resource ID. Config accepts only Amazon Web Services account ID. The compliance of the Amazon Web Services resource. The valid values are COMPLIANT, NON_COMPLIANT, and NOT_APPLICABLE. Annotation (string) --- Supplementary information about the reason of compliance. For example, this task was completed on a specific date. The time when the compliance was recorded.

nested_params.name: ComplianceResourceType
nested_params.description: The evaluated compliance resource type. Config accepts AWS::::Account resource type.

nested_params.name: ComplianceResourceId
nested_params.description: The evaluated compliance resource ID. Config accepts only Amazon Web Services account ID.

nested_params.name: ComplianceType
nested_params.description: The compliance of the Amazon Web Services resource. The valid values are COMPLIANT, NON_COMPLIANT, and NOT_APPLICABLE.

nested_params.name: Annotation
nested_params.description: Supplementary information about the reason of compliance. For example, this task was completed on a specific date.

nested_params.name: OrderingTimestamp
nested_params.description: The time when the compliance was recorded.
